    {
      "id": 16,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Token Types & Prompt Caching Guide",
      "gridPos": {"h": 18, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 9},
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "**Documentation:** [Prompt Caching](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/build-with-claude/prompt-caching) | [API Pricing](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/about-claude/pricing) | [Claude Code Telemetry](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code/telemetry)\n\n---\n\n### Token Types\n\n| Type | Description | Cost Impact |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| **Input** | New tokens sent to the model that aren't in cache (user messages, new file contents, tool results). Only includes tokens *after* the last cache breakpoint. | Full input price |\n| **Output** | Tokens generated by the model (responses, tool calls, code edits) | Full output price |\n| **Cache Read** | Tokens served from Anthropic's server-side prompt cache. The system prompt, tool schemas, and prior conversation context are reused across requests sharing the same prefix. | **90% cheaper** than input (0.1x) |\n| **Cache Creation** | Tokens written into the prompt cache for the first time. On subsequent requests with the same prefix, these become cache reads. | **25% more** than input (1.25x for 5-min TTL) |\n\n---\n\n### How Prompt Caching Works\n\nPrompt caching is managed **server-side by Anthropic** — there is no local storage. When Claude Code sends a request, large static content (system prompt, tool definitions, prior conversation turns) is cached. Follow-up requests that share the same prefix hit the cache instead of re-processing everything.\n\n- **5-minute TTL** (default): Cache write costs 1.25x input price. Breaks even after just **1 cache read**.\n- **1-hour TTL**: Cache write costs 2x input price. Breaks even after **2 cache reads**.\n- Cache hits are **free to refresh** — accessing cached content resets the TTL at no extra cost.\n- Minimum cacheable tokens: **4,096** for Opus 4.6 / Haiku 4.5, **2,048** for Sonnet 4.6, **1,024** for Sonnet 4.5/4.\n\n---\n\n### Pricing per Million Tokens (USD)\n\n| Model | Input | 5m Cache Write | 1h Cache Write | Cache Read | Output |\n|-------|-------|---------------|---------------|------------|--------|\n| **Claude Opus 4.6** | $5.00 | $6.25 | $10.00 | **$0.50** | $25.00 |\n| **Claude Sonnet 4.6** | $3.00 | $3.75 | $6.00 | **$0.30** | $15.00 |\n| **Claude Haiku 4.5** | $1.00 | $1.25 | $2.00 | **$0.10** | $5.00 |\n\nA high **cache read / input ratio** on this dashboard means good cache efficiency and significant cost savings.",
        "code": {"showLineNumbers": false}
      }
    },
    {
